<number box="[353,412,620,646]" pageId="6" value="1946.0">1946</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,690,859]" pageId="6">
This genus is clearly monophyletic, possess a uniquely flattened mesopleuron, without an impressed mesopleural suture separating the mesepisternum from a narrow mesepimeron, with lateral longitudinal carinae extending its entire length of TII and at least on the anterior 
<number box="[748,783,763,787]" pageId="6" value="0.3">0.3</number>
of 
<collectionCode box="[835,883,763,786]" pageId="6">TIII</collectionCode>
, upper edge of pronotum without or with an inconspicuous submarginal groove. 
<taxonomicName box="[555,636,799,822]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Trieces" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[555,636,799,822]" italics="true" pageId="6">Trieces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are parasitoids of a wide variety of smaller Lepidoptera (
<bibRefCitation author="Gauld" pageId="6" refString="Gauld, I., Sithole, R., Gomes, J. U. &amp; Godoy, C. (2002) The Ichneumonidae of Costa Rica, 4. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 66, 1 - 768." type="journal article" year="2002">
Gauld 
<emphasis box="[151,200,834,859]" italics="true" pageId="6">et al</emphasis>
., 
<number box="[221,282,835,859]" pageId="6" value="2002.0">2002</number>
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
